    <div id="collapse1" class="collapse tf-panel-collapse-body">
        <p>The FID offers various access options to full texts, which we aim to continuously improve and expand in the future. In KrimDok, there is already the possibility to directly access a researched electronic journal article through a link. In the future, the database will also include references to criminologically relevant e-books. In cases where the works are not available under open access conditions, they can be accessed through your library's subscription or licensing. Additionally, a selection of currently available open access journals has been compiled, which includes relevant journals in the field as well as those related to criminology. The articles in these journals can be accessed from any location due to their unrestricted access. In the project components "DigiKrimDok" and "Criminological Repository," further relevant full texts are being collected through various strategies. You can conveniently search for and access all documents through the KrimDok database.</p>
